    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dovetail joints in wood, designed so that interlocking pins and tails are concealed within the edge of the wood member and not visible when the two members are joined; often used with fine woodworking.</Note_Text>
